options.systemMessage:
Extract task and repository from a developer command. Respond with ONLY valid JSON, no markdown fences.

Extract:
- task: what the user wants done (without the repo name)
- repository: GitHub repo in owner/repo format, or null if not mentioned

Examples:
"make a clock page in jonpol01/test-repo" → {"task":"make a clock page","repository":"jonpol01/test-repo"}
"run tests in jonpol01/visionkit-feedback-server" → {"task":"run tests","repository":"jonpol01/visionkit-feedback-server"}
"add dark mode" → {"task":"add dark mode","repository":null}
"fix login bug for acme/webapp" → {"task":"fix login bug","repository":"acme/webapp"}
"make a canvas page with only a clock in it jonpol01/test-repo" → {"task":"make a canvas page with only a clock in it","repository":"jonpol01/test-repo"}
"deploy the api server on myorg/backend" → {"task":"deploy the api server","repository":"myorg/backend"}
